{"parentUuid":"bbd72b3a-773b-4427-b0d6-5fe86a3946f4","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"2b92bb35-2200-4dda-ae8b-cbba73f37ecb","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/alisha/Projects/marvin/plugin/skills/marvin\n\n# Marvin\n\n`marvin` now supports a smaller workflow:\n\n- `plan`\n- `plan-tui`\n- `investigate`\n- `investigate-tui`\n- `implement`\n- `work`\n- `wt`\n- `clean`\n- `status`\n\nUse these commands directly. Do not reference older hook-based collaboration commands.\n\n## Commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n| --- | --- |\n| `/marvin plan` | Run the autonomous multi-agent plan loop and write a plan doc plus timeline. |\n| `/marvin plan-tui` | Configure and launch `marvin plan` from the TUI. |\n| `/marvin investigate` | Run the autonomous investigation loop and write findings plus timeline. |\n| `/marvin investigate-tui` | Configure and launch `marvin investigate` from the TUI. |\n| `/marvin implement [spec-path] --agents ...` | Create one implementation branch/worktree per agent. If `spec-path` is omitted, it resolves the current repo's plan collab. |\n| `/marvin work` | Print or launch an implementation prompt. In an implement worktree it uses the managed spec; otherwise it resolves a plan collab in the current repo. |\n| `/marvin wt` | Create, list, and remove ad hoc worktrees under the configured worktree root, grouped by repo name. |\n| `/marvin clean [collab-id...]` | Remove completed collabs, or remove specific collab IDs explicitly. |\n| `/marvin status [collab-id]` | Show collabs for the current repo by default, `--all` for every saved collab, or one collab in detail. |\n\n## Typical flow\n\nCreate a plan:\n\n```bash\nmarvin plan --topic \"Should we replace Postgres with FoundationDB?\"\n```\n\nLaunch implementation worktrees:\n\n```bash\nmarvin implement --agents \"claude-code,codex\"\n```\n\nInside one of those worktrees:\n\n```bash\nmarvin work\n```\n\nIf you stay in the main repo after planning, `/marvin work` also works there. If multiple plan collabs exist for the repo, marvin prompts you to choose one.\n\n## Live overview\n\n`plan`, `plan-tui`, `investigate`, and `investigate-tui` all use the same live overview screen when running interactively:\n\n- the main document\n- the timeline\n- live transcripts\n- stance history\n\nUse the TUI when the user wants a form-based setup flow instead of flags.\n\n## Notes\n\n- `marvin implement` is setup-only. Use normal git workflows to compare, merge, and clean up implementation branches.\n- All commands output JSON by default unless the command is intentionally interactive.\n- Supported agent types are `claude-code`, `codex`, and `gemini-cli`.\n\n\nARGUMENTS: work"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"5f328f62-1886-4543-955d-cadad1b0ecb5","timestamp":"2026-04-30T20:38:05.083Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_01C9tAdNno9UKmHhf21L5tDW","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"a88641f6-df38-4dda-89ef-d14176b173e6","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"alisha/commit"}
