specific code block by tracing the latest change for a file line,\n36\trange, or pasted snippet through git blame and Entire checkpoints.\n37\t\n38\tCurrent behavior:\n39\t\n40\t- resolves file lines, ranges, or pasted snippets to exact line numbers\n41\t- asks for a concrete file line, range, or snippet before running provenance commands\n42\t- deduplicates commit and checkpoint lookups before running expensive transcript commands\n43\t- asks before expanding broad ranges with many unique commits\n44\t- summarizes `entire explain` output without dumping raw transcripts by default; raw transcript expansion is opt-in\n45\t- falls back to clearly labeled current-code analysis when checkpoint-backed context is unavailable\n46\t\n47\tExamples:\n48\t\n49\t- \"tell me why this code is like that\"\n50\t- \"why does this code look like this?\"\n51\t- \"what happened here: `src/auth.ts:42-57`\"\n52\t- \"what happened at `src/auth.ts:42`\"\n53\t- \"what happened to this block?\" plus a pasted snippet\n54\t\n55\t### `search`\n56\t\n57\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n58\t\n59\tCurrent behavior:\n60\t\n61\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n62\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n63\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n64\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n65\t\n66\t## Installation\n67\t\n68\tInstall with [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI (universal, works with any [Agent Skills](https://agentskills.io)-compatible tool):\n69\t\n70\t```bash\n71\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n72\t# or a single skill:\n73\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill session-handoff\n74\t```\n75\t\n76\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n77\t\n78\t<details>\n79\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n80\t\n81\t```bash\n82\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n83\t/plugin install entire\n84\t```\n85\t\n86\t</details>\n87\t\n88\t<details>\n89\t<summary>Cursor</summary>\n90\t\n91\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n92\t\n93\t```bash\n94\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.cursor/skills/entire\n95\t```\n96\t\n97\tCursor auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`.\n98\t\n99\t</details>\n100\t\n101\t<details>\n102\t<summary>Gemini CLI</summary>\n103\t\n104\t```bash\n105\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n106\t```\n107\t\n108\tUpdate with `gemini extensions update entire`.\n109\t\n110\t</details>\n111\t\n112\t<details>\n113\t<summary>OpenCode</summary>\n114\t\n115\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n116\t\n117\t```bash\n118\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n119\t```\n120\t\n121\tOpenCode auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/`, `.opencode/skills/`, and `.claude/skills/`.\n122\t\n123\t</details>\n124\t\n125\t<details>\n126\t<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n127\t\n128\tClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n129\t\n130\t```bash\n131\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\tCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/.agents/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`. Update with `cd ~/.agents/skills/entire && git pull`.\n135\t\n136\t</details>\n137\t\n138\t<details>\n139\t<summary>Copilot</summary>\n140\t\n141\t```bash\n142\t/plugin install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n143\t# or\n144\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.copilot/skills/entire\n145\t```\n146\t\n147\tCopilot auto-discovers skills from `.copilot/skills/`.\n148\t\n149\t</details>\n150\t\n151\t<details>\n152\t<summary>Antigravity</summary>\n153\t\n154\tClone and symlink into the cross-client discovery path:\n15