{"parentUuid":"7c7dc5ce-848e-4605-86bc-442c537128fe","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Co1Uq14jVvyyKASyEx6fZc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Review of the v0.4.0 dogfood run\n\nI just ran the skill on its own implementation. Here's what worked, what didn't, and what to change.\n\n### What worked\n\n- **Preflight (Step 1)** — parallel `entire/gh/repo/base/branch` checks were clean. The base-branch resolution chain (`gh repo view` → `git symbolic-ref` → `main`) is the right shape.\n- **Push + PR open** (Steps 4, 6, 7) — uneventful, which is what you want.\n- **Fallback design** — the \"zero checkpoint-backed commits → git-only\" rule is unambiguous.\n- **Tooling rules** — pre-banning `entire search` and `git add -A` saved real footguns.\n\n### Where it broke down on this run\n\n1. **The newly-made commit had a checkpoint, but `Outcome: (not generated)` and `Intent: \"marvin work\"`.** The skill says \"Title — derived from the most recent checkpoint-backed commit's intent.\" Following that literally gives a PR titled `marvin work`. I had to deviate and use the commit subject. **A cold agent running this skill would have produced an awful title.**\n\n2. **Checkpoint ID format mismatch.** `entire explain --no-pager` displays IDs like `a88641f6-df3` (12 chars, truncated). Feeding that back to `entire explain a88641f6-df3 --short --no-pager` returns *\"no checkpoint or commit found matching 'a88641f6-df3'\"*. The skill recommends this path but it doesn't actually work without somehow expanding the ID first.\n\n3. **The `--generate` deferral hurts the just-made-commit case.** Step 5's whole value comes from `Outcome` (the synthesis). On commits made *during* this same skill invocation, Outcome is empty. So the most common case (one fresh commit + push + PR) lands in a hole the skill doesn't address: checkpoint exists, but produces no useful PR text.\n\n4. **`gh pr create` warned about an untracked