 Removes redundant repetition. |\n| 7 | Spell out the `Co-Authored-By` value: `the agent's published identity (e.g., \"Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\", \"Codex <noreply@openai.com>\")`. The current `<agent name>` placeholder is ambiguous across agents. | Cross-agent consistency. |\n| 8 | Add a `Response Format` clarification: the `Entire Commit:` header goes on the *final summary turn*, not interleaved with progress messages. | Removes ambiguity I had to resolve myself. |\n\n### Net assessment\n\nThe skill's *structure* is solid — preflight, fallback path, banned commands, draft-only PR creation. The *Entire-mining logic* is the weak part: it over-trusts `Intent` and assumes `Outcome` will be populated, neither of which holds on a fresh commit. The single most impactful change is #1 (treat prompt-only intent as no-checkpoint) — without it, the skill silently produces worse PR titles than the upstream git-only equivalent on the most common invocation pattern.\n\nWant me to land #1, #2, #4, #6, and #8 as a follow-up patch (these are all skill-text edits, no behavior loss) and defer #3 to a v2 issue?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":364,"cache_read_input_tokens":122459,"output_tokens":4900,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":364,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":4900,"cache_read_input_tokens":122459,"cache_creation_input_tokens":364,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":364},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CaadjT5QVeaYWnmceUUeb","type":"assistant","uuid":"ed8960ab-5fbd-495b-9c77-1966f811e460","timestamp":"2026-04-30T21:05:43.957Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills",